{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bb50349b-d6cf-49bb-b930-e91b7647ce62","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events on the returned `Window`:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Activated    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated  += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Resumed      += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Destroying   += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Lifecycle flow:**\n\n| Transition | Event |\n|---|---|\n| App launches | `Created` → `Activated` |\n| User switches away | `Deactivated` → `Stopped` |\n| User returns | `Resumed` → `Activated` |\n| App closed | `Destroying` |\n| iOS/Mac background | `Backgrounding` (+ save state via `BackgroundingEventArgs.State`) |\n\n> **Tip:** `Backgrounding` is iOS/macOS-only. On Android/Windows the equivalent path is `Stopped`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"216d2a41-8778-46df-be83-f4fa1650d8b0","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for logging/debugging. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI development — I can answer it directly without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":434,"requestId":"045A:34A53A:AFFD9A:C8B9E1:6A0279DE"},"id":"656024d8-8965-45e3-a0b4-e57726e41498","timestamp":"2026-05-12T00:52:56.018Z","parentId":"371015a7-85fc-48ec-b52c-201edf046299"}
